00:20:20.900 --> 00:20:25.859
is valid, that it's a snapshot of the packages that were used to publish it, and even though

00:20:25.859 --> 00:20:33.380
I upgrade R on the host machine and deploy other packages or other apps with different

00:20:33.380 --> 00:20:40.780
levels of software, that one that I encapsulated when I published it before stays that way

00:20:40.780 --> 00:20:46.619
unless I make a specific decision to update components.

00:20:46.619 --> 00:20:50.260
Just a plug for integration of Workbench with Connect.

00:20:50.260 --> 00:20:51.260
Absolutely.

